how improve it? not aesthetics, but efficiency and studliness
To push this setup from "functional" to "studly and hyper-efficient," you need to minimize friction between your brain and the computer. Since you’re already using Hyprland, Neovim, and Yazi, you have the foundation.
Here is how to level up the efficiency:
1. Master the "Context Switch"
Efficiency is killed by searching for windows.
Persistent Scratchpads: Use Hyprland's special workspaces for things you need instantly but not constantly (like a calculator, btop, or a music player). Bind them to a single key so they toggle over your current work.
Smart Workspaces: Use window rules to force specific apps (Browser, Discord, Dev tools) to specific workspaces. You should never have to "look" for your browser; it should always be on Workspace 2.
2. Deep Integration (The "Unix Way")
Make your tools talk to each other so you don't have to leave the terminal.
Yazi + Neovim: Set up a keybind in Yazi to open files in your existing Neovim instance rather than a new one. This keeps your workflow in a single "brain."
Zoxide: Replace cd with zoxide. It learns your habits so you can jump to your deepest project folder by just typing z brainy.
FZF (Fuzzy Finder): If you aren't using fzf everywhere, you're losing time. Use it to search command history, find files, and even switch git branches instantly.
3. Automate the Mundane
Keychord / Leader Keys: Instead of complex Ctrl+Alt+Shift+S combos, use a "Leader" key in Neovim and Tmux. It’s much faster to tap Space, then s, then s than to claw-grip your keyboard.
Shell Aliases: If you type a command more than three times a day, alias it. gcp for git commit && git push, for example.
Headless Scripting: Use hyprctl (the Hyprland CLI) to write scripts that rearrange your entire layout for specific tasks, like a "Coding Mode" or a "Deep Work Mode" that closes all distractions.
4. The "Studly" Factor: Minimize UI
True efficiency often looks like nothing is happening.
Remove the Bars: If you know what workspace you’re on, you don't need a status bar. Use waybar with "autohide" or remove it entirely and use notifications (mako or dunst) for system info.
Keyboard-Only Browser: Use the Vimium extension in your browser. Navigating the web with j/k and f to click links is the ultimate efficiency flex.
