does all this go in hyprland.conf ?
Most of it does, but it’s split between two files to handle the logic and the visuals.
1. The Keybindings (hyprland.conf)
The Submap logic and the Leader keys go directly into your hyprland.conf. This is where you define what the keys actually do.
nix
# --- Inside hyprland.conf ---

# Start the sequence
bind = $mainMod, SPACE, submap, LEADER...

submap = LEADER...
    # Nesting into the screenshot category
    bind = , S, submap, LEADER > SCREENSHOT
    bind = , escape, submap, reset 
submap = reset

submap = LEADER > SCREENSHOT
    # The actual actions
    bind = , A, exec, grimblast copy area
    bind = , A, submap, reset

    bind = , S, exec, grimblast copy screen
    bind = , S, submap, reset

    bind = , escape, submap, reset 
submap = reset
Use code with caution.
2. The Visual Feedback (~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc)
The Waybar module needs to be enabled in your Waybar configuration file (usually config or config.jsonc).
You need to add "hyprland/submap" to your modules-left (or center/right) list and then define how it looks in the same file:
json
"hyprland/submap": {
    "format": "<span style=\"italic\">{}</span>", 
    "tooltip": false
},
Use code with caution.
3. The Styling (~/.config/waybar/style.css)
To make it look "studly" (e.g., making the text glow red when you are in a submap), you add this to your Waybar CSS:
