By themselves, no—Hyprland submaps are purely "internal" logic states; they have no built-in visual menu or "hint" system. If you enter a submap and forget which key does what, you’re just stuck until you hit Escape.
However, if you want that "studly" efficiency where the UI helps you without getting in the way of the screenshot, you have two great options:
Option 1: The "Waybar Breadcrumbs" (Low Profile)
As we touched on earlier, you can make Waybar show the available keys. This is the most efficient because it’s already on your screen and doesn't count as a "window" that might mess up a screenshot.
In hyprland.conf:
